457
00:31:42,567 --> 00:31:47,947
To show foreigners that Korea
is a clean and developed country.

458
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:51,992
The poor, beggars, and street gum vendors.

459
00:31:51,993 --> 00:31:55,746
They didn't want people like that
to be seen.

460
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,539
MINISTRY OF HOME AFFAIRS DIRECTIVE NO. 410

461
00:31:57,540 --> 00:32:00,125
They carried out a crackdown on vagrants

462
00:32:00,126 --> 00:32:04,129
under Directive No. 410,
issued by the Ministry of Home Affairs.

463
00:32:04,130 --> 00:32:05,590
DEFINITION OF A VAGRANT

464
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:11,011
I see it as a kind of human cleanup,
meant to remove citizens,

465
00:32:11,012 --> 00:32:16,768
including the innocent and vulnerable,
from the streets.

466
00:32:19,938 --> 00:32:20,939
Back then,

467
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:24,566
everyone loved Director Park In-geun.

468
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:26,068
VAGRANTS BEING SENT TO BROTHERS' HOME

469
00:32:26,069 --> 00:32:29,363
Just one call was enough
to take care of them.

470
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:32,492
The program was a major success
in Busan at the time.

471
00:32:33,618 --> 00:32:35,911
No other country
does it better than we do.

472
00:32:35,912 --> 00:32:40,083
There's not a single beggar
on the streets.

473
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,128
Do you see any beggars in Korea?
